  "description": "I feel like recently I\u0026rsquo;ve become almost allergic to actually typing things out on my computer.\nIt\u0026rsquo;s actually the 24th, that\u0026rsquo;s how allergic I\u0026rsquo;ve become. And, in fact, I can tell, there\u0026rsquo;s a sluggishness to my fingers as I type. Is it age? Perhaps, or I\u0026rsquo;m just\u0026hellip; really tired.\nAnyway I\u0026rsquo;m writing just to log that I\u0026rsquo;ve purchased a new 3D printer, the Creality K2 Pro, which has a huge 350x350mm build bed, and so in prep for that, am installing OrcaSlicer and taking more time to more considerately start setting up some more print profiles, filament profiles, and so on.\n",
